On this page, you will need to introduce your worklog. How did you complete it? How many weeks did you take to complete the program? What did you do in those weeks?
Typically, and as a standard, a worklog is carried out over about 3 months (throughout the internship period) with weekly contents as follows:
Week 1: Getting familiar with AWS and basic AWS services
Week 2: Cloud9, S3 Hosting, EC2 Auto Scaling, CloudWatch &amp; CLI Automation
Week 3: DynamoDB, ElastiCache, Networking, CloudFront, AD, and Migration Labs
Week 4: Serverless Automation, CloudWatch Advanced Monitoring, IAM Access Control, Systems Management, and Infrastructure as Code
